+{"id":"markdown_web_browser-7sx","content_hash":"3e38ba1f6ca765ef2ec1c8eef6f5d90f99d7c82ccf8ef663124272a9654d7e74","title":"Prometheus metrics instrumentation","description":"Plan §§19.2, 19.9, 20.2 call for Prometheus metrics on capture/OCR/stitch timings, warnings, and SSE health. Wire prometheus-fastapi-instrumentator into app/main.py (expose /metrics), define counters/histograms for capture duration, OCR duration, stitch duration, warning incidents, and SSE heartbeat gaps, and increment them from JobManager/capture pipeline. Provide tests ensuring the metrics endpoint responds and that metric counters move after a simulated job run. Update README, PLAN §19/§20, and docs/ops.md with the new monitoring hooks.","status":"in_progress","priority":2,"issue_type":"feature","assignee":"WhiteCastle","created_at":"2025-11-07T16:36:27.402691383-06:00","updated_at":"2025-11-07T16:36:30.662447063-06:00","source_repo":".","labels":["metrics","ops"],"comments":[{"id":121,"issue_id":"markdown_web_browser-7sx","author":"ubuntu","text":"WhiteCastle taking this: goal is to expose Prom metrics via prometheus-fastapi-instrumentator, add capture/ocr/stitch histograms + warning counters, and document the endpoint + dashboard hooks (PLAN §19.9/§20.2). Will touch app/main.py, app/jobs.py, app/settings.py, docs/ops.md, README.md, PLAN §19/§20, and add pytest coverage for the metrics endpoint + instrumentation.","created_at":"2025-11-07T22:36:35Z"},{"id":124,"issue_id":"markdown_web_browser-7sx","author":"ubuntu","text":"Implemented the first Prometheus instrumentation pass: added app/metrics.py with capture/OCR/stitch histograms, warning/blocklist counters, SSE heartbeat + job completion counters, wired JobManager/capture + SSE heartbeat emitters, and exposed the registry through prometheus-fastapi-instrumentator plus a background exporter on PROMETHEUS_PORT. Updated docs (README, docs/config.md, docs/ops.md) and PLAN §20.2 so ops knows how to scrape /metrics or the 9000 exporter. Tests: uv run ruff check --fix --unsafe-fixes, uvx ty check, uv run pytest tests/test_metrics.py.","created_at":"2025-11-07T22:42:58Z"}]}
 {"id":"markdown_web_browser-848","content_hash":"88881beeeac4616ca8c1bea47452ce1fe0a763ce6723d7ff9466030635639bb5","title":"mdwb CLI webhook delete","description":"Add a \\ command that hits the DELETE /jobs/{id}/webhooks endpoint (id or url selection), mirrors the server’s validation/error messages, and adds pytest coverage for the request builder so operators can remove stale webhooks from the CLI per PLAN \\u00a79.1.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"BlueHill","created_at":"2025-11-07T15:11:30.863249331-06:00","updated_at":"2025-11-07T15:13:38.778120306-06:00","closed_at":"2025-11-07T15:13:38.778130796-06:00","source_repo":".","labels":["cli","webhooks"],"comments":[{"id":102,"issue_id":"markdown_web_browser-848","author":"ubuntu","text":"BlueHill: wired up mdwb jobs webhooks delete (uses DELETE /jobs/{id}/webhooks with --id/--url validation), added CLI docs + PLAN note, and expanded tests/test_mdwb_cli_webhooks.py to exercise the request payload. Tests: 'uv run pytest tests/test_mdwb_cli_webhooks.py'.","created_at":"2025-11-07T21:13:32Z"}]}
